page.title: 13Horsell High Street.
page.content: Horsell is quite highly populated for its size. In the High Street, you have every shop you need. For instance there is a solicitors, building society, freezer centre,green grocers, two hair-dressers, an off licence, post office, newsagents, supermarket, butchers, and even a shoe shop and a clothes shop. Horsell also has it's own play park, tennis courts, cricket ground, bowling green and its own Guide and Scout pack. In Horsell High street is a very old church. You can hear the church bells ringing for miles around. There is also an Evangelical church. There are a few schools including private and secondary schools. Horsell has it's own trading estate, with at least twenty wharehouses.
